reviewText:
A very generic puzzle game, where mediocre could be said about everything in it - from graphics to sounds to gameplay.
The graphics in particular aren't very crisp, and sometimes I found myself lost between the foreground and background. Nothing really stands out as exciting, and while nothing is particularly bad, nothing about it is particularly good.
I played the whole game in about 3hrs - probably more than the average person, as I initially wanted to collect everything, but gave up on this idea part-way through due to lack of interest.

Might be worth playing if you like Lemmings, or similar style puzzle games, but not for full price - maybe a couple $.

Recommended? Probably not, unless you want to play something truly, well, meh.

reviewText:
3.7 - A Tribute to a Good Game...

Remember that amazing game Lemmings? This isn't it. It's just a cheap knockoff. The music is the same on every level. The Furries sound like Despicable Me minions (annoying) and the puzzles are too easy.

I don't hate this game; I just don't like it very much. It feels way more dated than 3 years old. I would feel mucho cheated paying $7.

I'd pay $0.50.
